<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Help</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/style.css">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Quicksand:wght@300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/4eaf49172f.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="../../img/favicon.ico">

</head>

<body>
    <div class="content-flex">
        {{>navigation}}
        <div class="main-flex">
            <div class="main">
                <h1>{{title}}</h1>
                <h6>Location not found / Wrong Location</h6>
                <p>If you are getting "Location not found" as the output or the weather details displayed are for the wrong location, please specify your location a bit more like adding the state or the country name separated by spaces to make it more precise.</p>
                <h6>Forecast not found</h6>
                <p>If you are getting "Forecast not found" as the output, I am sorry but the weather API doesn't have the data for the entered location.</p>
            </div>
            {{>footer}}
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="./js/toggleMenu.js"></script>

</body>

</html>